# 📱 Instagram Data Analysis Project

## 📌 Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing Instagram data to extract meaningful insights about user engagement, content performance, and growth patterns.

The analysis helps understand what type of content performs best and how different metrics influence engagement.

---

## 🎯 Objective

* Analyze Instagram dataset for engagement insights
* Identify factors affecting likes, comments, and reach
* Understand content performance trends
* Visualize key social media metrics

---

## 📂 Dataset

The dataset includes:

* Post ID / Caption
* Likes 👍
* Comments 💬
* Shares / Reach (if available)
* Post type (image, video, reel)
* Date / Time of posting

---

## ⚙️ Technologies Used

* Python 🐍
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Jupyter Notebook

---

## 🔍 Steps Performed

### 1. Data Loading

* Imported dataset using Pandas
* Checked dataset structure

### 2. Data Cleaning

* Handled missing values
* Converted date columns to datetime
* Cleaned text/caption data

### 3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

* Engagement analysis (likes, comments)
* Post type performance comparison
* Time-based analysis (best posting time)

### 4. Data Visualization

* 📊 Bar Charts → Engagement by post type
* 📈 Line Graphs → Trends over time
* 🔥 Heatmaps → Correlation between metrics
* 📉 Distribution Plots → Likes/comments spread

---

## 📊 Key Insights

* Certain post types (e.g., reels/videos) may generate higher engagement
* Posting time impacts reach and interaction
* Strong correlation between likes and comments
* Engagement patterns can guide content strategy

